220
00:20:01,181 --> 00:20:08,205
So it's, I would say it's more of a practitioner's side, but it's incredibly helpful.

221
00:20:09,306 --> 00:20:23,354
And I've not referred back to it since in my time with the city, but I can look back and see if their language was a little bit simpler in terms of service animals.

222
00:20:23,794 --> 00:20:27,216
But only because there is a clear distinction and it always created

223
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:38,106
It always created confusion with people assuming that they had certain rights that they actually didn't have.

224
00:20:38,126 --> 00:20:42,289
And not just confusion in the workspace, confusion in many other spaces as well, right?

225
00:20:42,309 --> 00:20:51,777
You could bring your service animal into many businesses, many locations, but actually you can't, your emotional support animal is not granted the same rights.

226
00:20:51,897 --> 00:20:58,703
So you would not necessarily be able to walk your miniature horse through the mall.

227
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:13,715
And the reason I picked that is because equinines are actually like very up there, really preferred in terms of providing support.

228
00:21:14,335 --> 00:21:23,762
I don't know if folks have heard of equinine therapy and emotional support, miniature horses are really in as emotional support animals.

229
00:21:26,363 --> 00:21:31,367
And pigs, specific kind of pig as well, I just can't remember which one.

230
00:21:34,112 --> 00:21:55,886
